# Autodarts Patterns

## Architecture

- `main.js` — adapter entry (`Autodarts extends utils.Adapter`); polling loop, state routing
- `lib/throw.js` — single throw logic
- `lib/visit.js` — visit logic (3 darts)
- `lib/trafficLight.js` — traffic light state management
- `lib/hardware.js` — hardware control (lighting, power)
- `lib/config.js` — configuration validation
- `lib/httpHelper.js` — HTTP helper functions
- `lib/systemInfo.js` — system info (version, host)
- `lib/tools.js` — Tools addon integration

## API communication

- Local Board Manager at `http://<host>:<port>/`
- No authentication required (local network only)
- Endpoints: `/api/state`, `/api/version`, `/api/config`, `/api/host`
- Use native `node:http` via `lib/httpHelper.makeRequest()`
- On network error: set `online` to `false`, traffic light to red

## Polling

- Managed in `main.js` via chained `setTimeout` (not `setInterval`)
- Interval: `adapter.config.intervalSec` (seconds, default 1)
- Slower interval when offline (`offlineIntervalMs`)
- Signature-based deduplication prevents processing duplicate throw data

## State creation

Use `extendObjectAsync` (not `setObjectNotExistsAsync`):

```javascript
await this.extendObjectAsync("throw.current", {
  type: "state",
  common: {
    name: { en: "Current throw score", de: "Aktueller Wurf-Score" },
    type: "number",
    role: "value",
    read: true,
    write: false,
  },
  native: {},
});
```

## State naming

- Throws: `throw.*`, visits: `visit.*`
- Traffic light: `trafficLight.*`
- Connection: `online`
- System info: `systemInfo.*`
- Hardware: `hardware.*`
- Tools addon: `tools.*`

## Pitfalls

- Do not add axios or other HTTP libraries
- Always provide bilingual state names (`en` + `de`)
- Clean up `pollTimer`, `versionTimer`, and `resetTimers` in `onUnload`
- Use `setState()` without callback (returns Promise) — not deprecated `setStateAsync()`
